<TITLE> SATRC agrees to prioritise rural connectivity </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 14 (bdnews24.com)  Telecommunications regulators of South Asian countries are considering putting top priority on rural connectivity. Chairmen of telecoms regulators of the countries discussed the issue at the ninth South Asian Telecommunications Regulators' Council (SATRC) meeting that concluded in Dhaka Friday. Newly elected SATRC chair, also Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission chief, Manjurul Alam told bdnews24.com that the chiefs of the South Asian regulators had given maximum priority to rural connectivity. Besides, he said, they had also agreed on reducing tariffs. bdnews24.
